Chelsea boss, Thomas Tuchel, has named the player who will be in his side’s squad to face Aston Villa in the Premier League final day fixture on Sunday. According to Tuchel, Andreas Christensen will be included in the Chelsea squad against Aston Villa at Villa Park after the defender participated in full training on Thursday and Friday. The German disclosed this on Friday during his pre-match press conference. Chelsea head to the game following a 2-1 win over Leicester City in their last Premier League encounter. The Blues are currently in the third position on the Premier League table with 67 points from 37 games. “Andreas Christensen will be in the squad,” said Tuchel. “He did full training today and also yesterday without any problems, so he will be back.” The kick-off time for Aston Villa vs Chelsea is 4 pm. EPL: Why I benched Sadio Mane in Liverpool’s 2-1 win over Aston Villa – Klopp 